<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 14 at 6:41AM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...An area of heavy snow showers will affect southwestern
Medina...Wayne and southwestern Lorain Counties Until 815 AM EDT....
At 637 AM EDT, radar indicated a band of snow extending from Oberlin
to Lodi, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Visibility dropping to below one half mile...
One to two inches of quick snow accumulation...
Locations impacted include...
Lorain, Wooster, Vermilion, Amherst, Orrville, Rittman, Wellington,
Doylestown, Lodi, Creston, Dalton, West Salem, Chippewa Lake,
Oberlin, Seville, Lagrange, Penfield, South Amherst, Pittsfield and
Smithville.
Motorists traveling on Interstate 71 near Lodi should use extra
caution. Rapid changes in visibility and snow covered roads may lead
to accidents.</description>
